snippet: Bills coach Rex Ryan challenged the NFL to consider ejecting players for blindside hits to the head such as the one by Dolphins receiver Jarvis Landry that leveled Buffalo safety Aaron Williams....
lead_paragraph: Bills coach Rex Ryan challenged the NFL to consider ejecting players for blindside hits to the head such as the one by Dolphins receiver Jarvis Landry that leveled Buffalo safety Aaron Williams.

headline.main: Bills Coach Ryan Calls Landry's Hit on Williams 'Dirty'
headline.print_headline: Bills Coach Ryan Calls Landry's Hit on Williams 'Dirty'
